data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your expression-tree building code **won't compile**. The new overload accepts a plain lambda, so conditional setters become trivial:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

Two related changes:

- **Duplicate names get a numeric suffix.** Both `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one column; now they get `Street` and `Street1`. This **will break existing tables**.
- **Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`; now it's `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** — pin column names to preserve your existing schema:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin the old name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter containing potentially-redacted SQL for logging.

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText (redacted) for logging,
        // command.CommandText for actual execution logic
    }
}
```

Update **all** method signatures on the interface accordingly.
